data_table.description: Multiplexed Immunoassay Panel 5 (SABRe Project 2), Offspring Cohort Exam 7, Generation 3 Cohort Exam 1. This is the fifth in a series of immunoassay panels done on the same group of participants (Offspring Exam 7 and Gen 3 Exam 1). To get a full set of all the immunoassays done, please combine the following datasets: l_mpimn01_2005_m_0692s, l_mpimn02_2005_m_0693s, l_mpimn03_2005_m_0694s, l_mpimn04_2005_m_0757s, l_mpimn05_2005_m_0758s, l_mpimn06_2005_m_0792s, l_mpimn07_2005_m_0802s, and l_mpimn08_2005_m_0836s.

variable.name: gp5
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for GP5 is 48.8 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 200000 pg/mL. GP5 values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use GP5_I to see what records are below and above these limits. GP5 values were set to unknown if GP5_CV was greater than or equal to 28.9 for Offspring (IDTYPE = 1) or 29.6 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3).

variable.name: gp5_cv
variable.comment: GP5_CV values were set to unknown if GP5_CV was greater than or equal to 28.9 for Offspring (IDTYPE = 1) or 29.6 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3).

variable.name: gapdh
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for GAPDH is 193 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 806000 pg/mL. GAPDH values were set to unknown if GAPDH_CV was greater than or equal to 35.2 for Offspring (IDTYPE = 1) or 35.6 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3).

variable.name: gapdh_cv
variable.comment: GAPDH_CV values were set to unknown if GAPDH_CV was greater than or equal to 35.2 for Offspring (IDTYPE = 1) or 35.6 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3).
